article.description: Taveion Hollingsworth had 21 points as Western Kentucky beat North Texas 67-51 in the quarterfinals of the Conference USA Tournament on Thursday night.
article.headline: Hollingsworth leads Hilltoppers to 67-51 quarterfinal win
article.linkText: Hollingsworth leads Hilltoppers to 67-51 quarterfinal win
article.story: FRISCO, Texas -- Taveion Hollingsworth had 21 points as Western Kentucky beat North Texas 67-51 in the quarterfinals of the Conference USA Tournament on Thursday night. Josh Anderson had 13 points and seven rebounds for Western Kentucky (19-13). Charles Bassey added four blocks. Lamonte Bearden had eight assists for the Hilltoppers. The Mean Green's 29.5 field goal percentage represented the worst mark by a Western Kentucky opponent this season. Ryan Woolridge had 13 points and six assists for the Mean Green (21-12). Jorden Duffy added 11 points and seven rebounds. Zachary Simmons had 13 rebounds. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
